trá» riÃªng. Trong khung cáº£nh nÃºi non hÃ¹ng vÄ©, chÃ¹a BÃ¡i ÄÃ­nh lÃ  Äiá»m hÃ nh hÆ°Æ¡ng ná»i tiáº¿ng vÃ o má»i dá»p Äáº§u nÄm, nÆ¡i ngÆ°á»i ta tÃ¬m vá» vá»i lÃ²ng thÃ nh kÃ­nh vÃ  khÃ¡t vá»ng hÆ°á»ng thiá»n.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><h3>8. ThÃ¡p BÃ  Ponagar (KhÃ¡nh HÃ²a)</h3><p> </p><p> </p><p>LÃ  dáº¥u tÃ­ch cÃ²n sÃ³t láº¡i cá»§a vÆ°Æ¡ng quá»c ChÄm Pa hÆ°ng thá»nh má»t thá»i, thÃ¡p BÃ  Ponagar tá»a láº¡c trÃªn Äá»nh Äá»i ven sÃ´ng CÃ¡i Nha Trang. ÄÆ°á»£c xÃ¢y dá»±ng tá»« tháº¿ ká»· VIII, quáº§n thá» nÃ y thá» ná»¯ tháº§n Ponagar â vá» máº«u tháº§n sinh sÃ´i muÃ´n loÃ i. Nhá»¯ng bá»©c phÃ¹ ÄiÃªu, hoa vÄn ÄÆ°á»£c cháº¡m kháº¯c tinh xáº£o trÃªn cháº¥t liá»u gáº¡ch nung cho tháº¥y trÃ¬nh Äá» nghá» thuáº­t ChÄm Pa Äáº¡t Äáº¿n Äá»nh cao. Háº±ng nÄm, lá» há»i ThÃ¡p BÃ  váº«n thu hÃºt hÃ ng nghÃ¬n ngÆ°á»i hÃ nh hÆ°Æ¡ng vÃ  khÃ¡ch du lá»ch.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><h3>9. Dinh Váº¡n Thá»§y TÃº (BÃ¬nh Thuáº­n)</h3><p> </p><p> </p><p>KhÃ¡c biá»t vá»i chÃ¹a chiá»n hay Äá»n ÄÃ i, Dinh Váº¡n Thá»§y TÃº lÃ  nÆ¡i thá» cÃ¡ Ãng â linh váº­t trong tÃ­n ngÆ°á»¡ng dÃ¢n gian cá»§a ngÆ° dÃ¢n ven biá»n miá»n Trung. ÄÆ°á»£c xÃ¢y dá»±ng vÃ o nÄm 1762, nÆ¡i ÄÃ¢y hiá»n lÆ°u giá»¯ bá» xÆ°Æ¡ng cÃ¡ voi dÃ i hÆ¡n 20m â lá»n nháº¥t ÄÃ´ng Nam Ã. Má»i nÄm, dinh tá» chá»©c nhiá»u lá» há»i cáº§u ngÆ° trang trá»ng, thá» hiá»n lÃ²ng biáº¿t Æ¡n cá»§a ngÆ° dÃ¢n Äá»i vá»i biá»n cáº£.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><h3>10. ChÃ¹a Linh PhÆ°á»c (ÄÃ  Láº¡t)</h3><p> </p><p> </p><p>CÃ²n gá»i lÃ  âchÃ¹a Ve Chaiâ vÃ¬ ÄÆ°á»£c trang trÃ­ báº±ng hÃ ng triá»u máº£nh sÃ nh sá»©, chÃ¹a Linh PhÆ°á»c mang váº» Äáº¹p Äá»c ÄÃ¡o vÃ  ká»³ cÃ´ng. Ná»i báº­t nháº¥t lÃ  tÆ°á»£ng Quan Tháº¿ Ãm Bá» TÃ¡t cao 17m lÃ m tá»« 600.000 bÃ´ng hoa báº¥t tá»­ â loÃ i hoa Äáº·c trÆ°ng cá»§a ÄÃ  Láº¡t. NgoÃ i ra, chÃ¹a cÃ²n cÃ³ mÃ´ hÃ¬nh âÄá»a ngá»¥c 18 táº§ngâ tÃ¡i hiá»n nhÃ¢n quáº£ luÃ¢n há»i, giÃºp ngÆ°á»i chiÃªm nghiá»m vá» cuá»c sá»ng vÃ  tÃ¢m linh.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><h3>11. Khu danh tháº¯ng TÃ¢y ThiÃªn (VÄ©nh PhÃºc)</h3><p> </p><p> </p><p>Náº±m giá»¯a rá»«ng quá»c gia Tam Äáº£o, TÃ¢y ThiÃªn vá»«a lÃ  nÆ¡i thá» Quá»c Máº«u LÄng Thá» TiÃªu â vá» ná»¯ tháº§n trong tÃ­n ngÆ°á»¡ng báº£n Äá»a, vá»«a lÃ  vÃ¹ng Äáº¥t khá»i nguyÃªn cá»§a Pháº­t giÃ¡o Viá»t Nam. Du khÃ¡ch hÃ nh hÆ°Æ¡ng pháº£i vÆ°á»£t qua nhá»¯ng báº­c ÄÃ¡, dÃ²ng suá»i mÃ¡t láº¡nh Äá» Äáº¿n chÃ¹a TÃ¢y ThiÃªn vÃ  thiá»n viá»n TrÃºc LÃ¢m TÃ¢y ThiÃªn. HÃ nh trÃ¬nh áº¥y khÃ´ng chá» lÃ  leo nÃºi, mÃ  cÃ²n lÃ  hÃ nh trÃ¬nh gá»t rá»­a tÃ¢m há»n, tÃ¬m vá» sá»± an yÃªn ná»i táº¡i.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Má»i cÃ´ng trÃ¬nh tÃ´n giÃ¡o Äá»u lÃ  má»t cÃ¢u chuyá»n, má»t tÃ¢m há»n. HÃ nh hÆ°Æ¡ng Äáº¿n nhá»¯ng Äiá»m Äáº¿n linh thiÃªng nÃ y, báº¡n khÃ´ng chá» chiÃªm ngÆ°á»¡ng váº» Äáº¹p kiáº¿n trÃºc, mÃ  cÃ²n cháº¡m Äáº¿n cá»t lÃµi vÄn hÃ³a, tÃ­n ngÆ°á»¡ng vÃ  niá»m tin cá»§a con ngÆ°á»i Viá»t Nam tá»« ngÃ n Äá»i. ÄÃ³ cÅ©ng lÃ  hÃ nh trÃ¬nh trá» vá» vá»i chÃ­nh mÃ¬nh â trong sá»± yÃªn láº·ng vÃ  thiÃªng liÃªng giá»¯a nhá»¯ng mÃ¡i cong rÃªu phong, giá»¯a tiáº¿ng chuÃ´ng chÃ¹a vá»ng vá» cuá»i trá»i.</p>','11 Điểm Đến Tôn Giáo Ấn Tượng tại Việt Nam','Việt Nam là miền đất của sự đa dạng tôn giáo, nơi những công trình tín ngưỡng không chỉ phục vụ nhu cầu tâm linh mà còn là những kiệt tác kiến trúc và di sản văn hóa quý báu','2026-06-05 15:38:44','2026-06-05 15:38:44'),(18,9,'en','A Journey to the Land of Spirituality and Architectural Heritage','a-journey-to-the-land-of-spirituality-and-architectural-heritage','Vietnam is a land of religious diversity, where spiritual sites not only serve as places of worship but also stand as masterpieces of architecture and invaluable cultural heritage.','<p>1. One Pillar Pagoda (Hanoi)</p><p> </p><p><br>A symbol of Vietnam\'s thousand-year-old civilization, the One Pillar Pagoda is one of the most unique architectural structures in the country. Built in 1049 based on a dream of Emperor Ly Thai Tong in which he saw the Bodhisattva Avalokitesvara sitting on a lotus, the pagoda stands on a single stone pillar in the middle of a lotus pond, symbolizing purity. Though small in size, the pagoda holds great spiritual significance and is considered one of Asiaâs architectural wonders.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>2. Tam Chuc Pagoda (Ha Nam)</p><p> </p><p><br>Nestled among towering limestone mountains and vast lakes, Tam Chuc Pagoda is often referred to as âa paradise on Earth.â It is currently the largest pagoda complex in Vietnam, rebuilt from an ancient pagoda dating back to the Dinh dynasty. The complex features Tam The Hall, Dharma Master Hall, and Avalokitesvara Hall â each adorned with thousands of stone reliefs depicting Buddhaâs life. During festivals or Vesak Day, tens of thousands of pilgrims visit seeking peace and mindfulness.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>3. Cao Dai Holy See (Tay Ninh)</p><p> </p><p><br>Located in southern Vietnam, the Cao Dai Holy See is the spiritual center of Caodaism â a unique Vietnamese religion. The structure impresses with its vibrant architecture, blending Eastern and Gothic Western styles. Inside, visitors will see the âDivine Eyeâ â the all-seeing eye symbolizing enlightenment â along with intricately carved dragon pillars. The Holy See is not only a place of worship for millions of followers but also a fascinating cultural and spiritual destination.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>4. Thien Mu Pagoda (Hue)</p><p> </p><p><br>Overlooking the poetic Perfume River, Thien Mu Pagoda is the oldest pagoda in Hue, built in 1601 by Lord Nguyen Hoang. Its most iconic feature is the Phuoc Duyen Tower â a seven-story octagonal tower that symbolizes the imperial city. The tranquil grounds and the resonating sound of its bell each afternoon evoke deep contemplation in the hearts of visitors.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>5. My Son Sanctuary (Quang Nam)</p><p> </p><p><br>Hidden in a lush green valley, My Son Sanctuary is a UNESCO World Heritage Site. Once the spiritual center of the Champa Kingdom, it features Hindu temples dedicated to the god Shiva. The structures, built with fired bricks using mysterious construction techniques still baffling scientists today, have withstood time and war, retaining a rare sacred and mystical beauty.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>6. Temple of Literature â Imperial Academy (Hanoi)</p><p> </p><p><br>Not only a temple honoring Confucius, the Temple of Literature also served as Vietnamâs first national university. Built in 1070, it symbolizes the countryâs respect for learning and the moral tradition of ârevering teachers.â The complex includes ancient buildings like the Khue Van Pavilion, the Well of Heavenly Clarity, and stone steles of laureates. The peaceful, tree-shaded atmosphere provides serenity for all who visit.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>7. Bai Dinh Pagoda (Ninh Binh)</p><p> </p><p><br>Part of the Trang An Scenic Landscape Complex, Bai Dinh Pagoda holds several records: the largest bronze Buddha statue in Asia, and the longest corridor of Arhat statues in Vietnam. The site is divided into an ancient and a modern section â each with its own significance. Surrounded by majestic mountains, Bai Dinh is a major pilgrimage site during the Lunar New Year, where people come with reverence and a wish to do good.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>8. Ponagar Cham Towers (Khanh Hoa)</p><p> </p><p><br>A remnant of the once-glorious Champa Kingdom, Ponagar Towers sit atop a hill by the Cai River in Nha Trang. Built in the 8th century, the complex worships the goddess Ponagar â the mother deity of fertility. Exquisite reliefs and carvings on fired brick reveal the artistic mastery of the Cham people. The annual Ponagar Festival draws thousands of pilgrims and tourists.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>9. Van Thuy Tu Temple (Binh Thuan)</p><p> </p><p><br>Different from pagodas or temples, Van Thuy Tu Temple honors the whale â a sacred creature in the folk beliefs of Central Vietnamâs fishing communities. Built in 1762, it houses the largest whale skeleton in Southeast Asia, over 20 meters long. The temple hosts solemn Whale Worship Festivals every year, expressing fishermenâs gratitude to the sea.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>10. Linh Phuoc Pagoda (Da Lat)</p><p> </p><p><br>Nicknamed the âVe Chai Pagodaâ (Glass Shard Pagoda), Linh Phuoc is decorated with millions of ceramic and porcelain pieces, giving it a uniquely intricate look. The most striking feature is a 17-meter-tall statue of Avalokitesvara made from 600,000 dried everlasting flowers â a symbolic flower of Da Lat. The pagoda also features a model of the â18 levels of hell,â helping visitors reflect on karma and the spiritual path.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>11. Tay Thien Scenic Complex (Vinh Phuc)</p><p> </p><p><br>Located within Tam Dao National Park, Tay Thien is both a sacred place worshipping Mother Goddess Lang Thi Tieu â a deity of local belief â and one of the earliest centers of Vietnamese Buddhism. Pilgrims must hike stone steps and cross cool mountain streams to reach Tay Thien Pagoda and the Truc Lam Zen Monastery. The journey is not just physical but also spiritual â a purification of the soul in search of inner peace.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Each religious site tells a story, embodies a soul. To pilgrimage to these sacred places is not just to admire architecture, but to touch the cultural core, beliefs, and enduring faith of the Vietnamese people. It is also a journey inward â into stillness and the sacred, beneath moss-covered roofs and the echo of temple bells fading into the horizon.</p>','A Journey to the Land of Spirituality and Architectural Heritage','Vietnam is a land of religious diversity, where spiritual sites not only serve as places of worship but also stand as masterpieces of architecture and invaluable cultural heritage.','2026-06-05 15:38:44','2026-06-05 15:38:44'),(19,10,'vi','Hướng dẫn tham quan Lăng Bác năm 2026 – Điểm đến thiêng liêng giữa lòng Hà Nội','huong-dan-tham-quan-lang-bac-nam-2026-iem-en-thieng-lieng-giua-long-ha-noi','Lăng Chủ tịch Hồ Chí Minh, thường gọi là Lăng Bác, không chỉ là công trình kiến trúc có ý nghĩa lịch sử sâu sắc mà còn là nơi hội tụ lòng thành kính của người dân Việt Nam và du khách quốc tế đối với vị lãnh tụ vĩ đại của dân tộc.','<h2>Äá»a chá» vÃ  thá»i gian má» cá»­a LÄng BÃ¡c 2026</h2><p> </p><ul><li><p>Äá»a chá»: Sá» 2 HÃ¹ng VÆ°Æ¡ng, Ba ÄÃ¬nh, HÃ  Ná»i</p></li></ul><p> </p><p><img src=\"https://travelplusvn.com/public/uploads/images/POST/HaNoi/02/main.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\"></p><p> </p><p> </p><ul><li><p>Giá» má» cá»­a:<br> </p><ul><li><p>MÃ¹a hÃ¨ (tá»« 01/4 Äáº¿n 31/10):<br> </p><ul><li><p>Thá»© 3 Äáº¿n thá»© 5: 7h30 â 10h30<br> </p></li><li><p>Thá»© 7, Chá»§ nháº­t, ngÃ y lá»: 7h30 â 11h<br><br><br> </p></li></ul></li><li><p>MÃ¹a ÄÃ´ng (tá»« 01/11 Äáº¿n 31/3):<br> </p><ul><li><p>Thá»© 3 Äáº¿n thá»© 5: 8h00 â 11h00<br> </p></li><li><p>Thá»© 7, Chá»§ nháº­t, ngÃ y lá»: 8h00 â 11h30<br><br> </p></li></ul></li></ul></li><li><p>Nghá» tham quan: Thá»© 2 vÃ  thá»© 6 háº±ng tuáº§n (trá»« cÃ¡c ngÃ y lá» lá»n)<br> </p></li></ul><p> </p><p><em>LÆ°u Ã½: NÃªn Äáº¿n sá»m Äá» xáº¿p hÃ ng vÃ  Äáº£m báº£o cÃ³ Äá»§ thá»i gian tham quan toÃ n bá» khu vá»±c.</em></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><h2>HÆ°á»ng dáº«n di chuyá»n Äáº¿n LÄng BÃ¡c</h2><p> </p><ul><li><p>Taxi hoáº·c xe mÃ¡y: Äáº¿n cá»ng chÃ­nh ÄÆ°á»ng HÃ¹ng VÆ°Æ¡ng. Báº¡n cÃ³ thá» gá»­i xe táº¡i khu vá»±c Báº£o tÃ ng Há» ChÃ­ Minh hoáº·c ÄÆ°á»ng HoÃ ng Diá»u gáº§n ÄÃ³.</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p>Xe buÃ½t cÃ´ng cá»ng: CÃ¡c tuyáº¿n Äi qua LÄng BÃ¡c bao gá»m: 09, 22, 33, 45, 50. ÄÃ¢y lÃ  lá»±a chá»n tiáº¿t