c LÄng.</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p>Giá»¯ tráº­t tá»±, khÃ´ng mang theo Äá» Än, nÆ°á»c uá»ng vÃ o bÃªn trong.</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p>Tráº» em dÆ°á»i 3 tuá»i khÃ´ng ÄÆ°á»£c vÃ o viáº¿ng LÄng.</p></li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p>LÄng Chá»§ tá»ch Há» ChÃ­ Minh khÃ´ng chá» lÃ  Äá»a chá» Äá» trong hÃ nh trÃ¬nh tÃ¬m hiá»u lá»ch sá»­ mÃ  cÃ²n lÃ  nÆ¡i Äá» má»i ngÆ°á»i dÃ¢n vÃ  du khÃ¡ch cáº£m nháº­n rÃµ nÃ©t tinh tháº§n yÃªu nÆ°á»c, sá»± hy sinh vÃ  giáº£n dá» cá»§a vá» Cha giÃ  dÃ¢n tá»c. HÃ£y dÃ nh thá»i gian ghÃ© thÄm vÃ  tráº£i nghiá»m khÃ´ng gian thiÃªng liÃªng nÃ y trong chuyáº¿n Äi HÃ  Ná»i cá»§a báº¡n nÄm 2026.</p>','Hướng dẫn tham quan Lăng Bác năm 2026 – Điểm đến thiêng liêng giữa lòng Hà Nội','Lăng Chủ tịch Hồ Chí Minh, thường gọi là Lăng Bác, không chỉ là công trình kiến trúc có ý nghĩa lịch sử sâu sắc mà còn là nơi hội tụ lòng thành kính của người dân Việt Nam và du khách quốc tế đối với vị lãnh tụ vĩ đại của dân tộc.','2026-06-05 15:43:43','2026-06-05 15:57:12'),(20,10,'en','A Visitor’s Guide to President Ho Chi Minh’s Mausoleum in 2026 – A Sacred Destination in the Heart of Hanoi','a-visitor-s-guide-to-president-ho-chi-minh-s-mausoleum-in-2026-a-sacred-destination-in-the-heart-of-hanoi','President Ho Chi Minh’s Mausoleum, commonly known as Lang Bac, is not only a historical architectural landmark but also a sacred place where both Vietnamese citizens and international visitors come to pay their respects to the great leader of the nation.','<h2>Location and Opening Hours in 2026</h2><p> </p><p>Address: No. 2 Hung Vuong Street, Ba Dinh District, Hanoi</p><p> </p><p><img src=\"https://travelplusvn.com/public/uploads/images/POST/HaNoi/02/main.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\"></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Opening hours:</p><p> </p><p>Summer (April 1 â October 31):</p><p> </p><ul><li><p>Tuesday to Thursday: 7:30 AM â 10:30 AM</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p>Saturday, Sunday &amp; public holidays: 7:30 AM â 11:00 AM</p></li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Winter (November 1 â March 31):</p><p> </p><ul><li><p>Tuesday to Thursday: 8:00 AM â 11:00 AM</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p>Saturday, Sunday &amp; public holidays: 8:00 AM â 11:30 AM</p></li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p>Closed on Mondays and Fridays <em>(except for national holidays)</em></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Note: Itâs recommended to arrive early to queue and have enough time to explore the entire complex.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><h3>How to Get There</h3><p> </p><ul><li><p>By taxi or motorbike: Head to the main entrance on Hung Vuong Street. Parking is available near the Ho Chi Minh Museum or Hoang Dieu Street.</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p>By public bus: Routes 09, 22, 33, 45, and 50 pass by the mausoleum. This is a budget-friendly and convenient option for travelers.</p></li></ul><p> </p><p><img src=\"https://travelplusvn.com/public/uploads/images/POST/HaNoi/02/02.png\" loading=\"lazy\"></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><h3>7 Unmissable Experiences at Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum</h3><p> </p><ol><li><p>Paying respects to President Ho Chi Minhâs embalmed body â A solemn and emotional moment for every Vietnamese citizen.<br><br> </p></li><li><p>Admiring the mausoleumâs architecture â A grand and powerful structure influenced by Soviet architectural style.<br><br> </p></li><li><p>Witnessing the flag-raising or lowering ceremony at Ba Dinh Square â A sacred daily ritual in the morning and evening.<br><br> </p></li><li><p>Visiting the Presidential Palace â Where Uncle Ho worked and received guests during his lifetime.<br><br> </p></li><li><p>Exploring Uncle Hoâs stilt house and fish pond â A peaceful and humble setting close to nature.<br><br> </p></li><li><p>Touring the Ho Chi Minh Museum â Home to valuable documents and artifacts on his life and legacy.<br><br> </p></li><li><p>Seeing the One Pillar Pagoda â A unique temple with rich cultural and historical significance.<br><br> </p></li></ol><h3> </h3><h3> </h3><h3>Nearby Food Recommendations</h3><p> </p><p>After your visit, try some traditional Hanoi specialties around the Ba Dinh area, such as:</p><p> </p><ul><li><p>Classic beef <em>pho</em></p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p>Hanoi-style <em>bun cha</em></p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p><em>Cha ca La Vong</em> (grilled fish)</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p><em>Thanh Tri</em> steamed rice rolls</p></li></ul><p> </p><p>These dishes offer a flavorful glimpse into Northern Vietnamâs culinary heritage.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><h3>Important Notes for Visitors</h3><p> </p><ul><li><p>Dress respectfully and modestly to match the sacred atmosphere.</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p>Phones, cameras, and video equipment are not allowed inside the mausoleum.</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p>Keep silent and do not bring food or drinks inside.</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p>Children under 3 years old are not permitted to enter the mausoleum.</p></li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>President Ho Chi Minhâs Mausoleum is more than a historical landmark â itâs a place where the spirit of patriotism, sacrifice, and humility of the âFather of the Nationâ can be deeply felt. Include this meaningful site in your 2026 Hanoi journey for an unforgettable cultural experience.</p>','A Visitor’s Guide to President Ho Chi Minh’s Mausoleum in 2026 – A Sacred Destination in the Heart of Hanoi','President Ho Chi Minh’s Mausoleum, commonly known as Lang Bac, is not only a historical architectural landmark but also a sacred place where both Vietnamese citizens and international visitors come to pay their respects to the great leader of the nation.','2026-06-05 15:43:43','2026-06-05 15:57:12'),(21,11,'vi','Du Lịch Chicago – Thành Phố Gió Hút Hồn Giữa Lòng Nước Mỹ','du-lich-chicago-thanh-pho-gio-hut-hon-giua-long-nuoc-my','Nhắc đến Chicago, người ta thường gọi đây là “Thành phố gió” – nơi hội tụ vẻ đẹp của kiến trúc hiện đại, lịch sử lâu đời và không khí nghệ thuật độc đáo.','<p>Tá»« bá» há» Michigan mÃªnh mÃ´