05 15:58:49'),(26,13,'en','Where to Travel in July? Top Domestic & International Destinations for Summer','where-to-travel-in-july-top-domestic-international-destinations-for-summer','July is the perfect time for summer travel, relaxation, and creating unforgettable memories. It’s the peak of the holiday season for students in Vietnam, and many places around the world are enjoying their most beautiful time of the year.','<h2>1. Explore Culture &amp; Beautiful Beaches in Da Nang</h2><p> </p><p>In July, Da Nang shines with blue beaches like My Khe, delicious local cuisine, and the festive spirit of summer events. The Danang International Fireworks Festival (DIFF 2025) continues to light up the Han River, offering dazzling nights filled with light and music.</p><p> </p><p><img src=\"https://travelplusvn.com/public/uploads/images/POST/T07/where/01.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\"></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Aside from the fireworks, the city offers vibrant experiences such as:</p><p> </p><ul><li><p>Morning beach swims</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p>Visiting Ba Na Hills and Marble Mountains</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p>Exploring Son Tra Peninsula</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p>Night strolls through Helio Night Market and enjoying local specialties like Mi Quang and grilled pork rice paper rolls</p></li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p>Bonus tip: Da Nang is the perfect base to combine your journey with a visit to Hoi An Ancient Town or Hue Imperial City, both just a short drive away.</p><p> </p><p><img src=\"https://travelplusvn.com/public/uploads/images/POST/T07/where/02.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\"></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><h2>2. Hit the Beach â The Hottest Trend of July</h2><p> </p><p>Julyâs sunny and dry weather makes it perfect for beach getaways. Top beach destinations in Vietnam include:</p><p> </p><ul><li><p>Northern &amp; North Central Coast: Quan Lan, Co To, Cat Ba, Ha Long, Sam Son, Cua Lo, Thien Cam, Nhat Le</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p>Central &amp; South Central Coast: Da Nang, Hoi An, Quy Nhon, Nha Trang, Mui Ne</p></li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p><img src=\"https://travelplusvn.com/public/uploads/images/POST/T07/where/03.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\"></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Many coastal cities also host exciting summer festivals, from Sáº§m SÆ¡n Carnival to beach performances in Cat Ba and Nha Trang Sea Festival.</p><p> </p><p>Note: July is high travel season in Vietnamâbook flights and hotels early, especially on weekends, to avoid surcharges and sold-out rooms.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><h2>3. Discover Bali â The Best Dry Season of the Year</h2><p> </p><p>Bali is at its best in July, with clear skies, warm temperatures (25â30Â°C), and minimal rain. Ideal for:</p><p> </p><ul><li><p>Beach days &amp; snorkeling in Bali, Lombok, or the Gili Islands</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p>Joining vibrant cultural festivals like Bali Arts Festival or Bali Kite Festival</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p>Family-friendly attractions like Waterbom Bali and Bali Safari &amp; Marine Park</p></li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><img src=\"https://travelplusvn.com/public/uploads/images/POST/T07/where/04.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\"></p><p> </p><p>Recommended stay: 5â7 days to enjoy the island to the fullest.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><h2>4. Jeju Island (South Korea) â Summer Fun with Nature &amp; Culture</h2><p> </p><p>Jeju comes alive in July with:</p><p> </p><ul><li><p>Beautiful beaches officially open from July 1st (Hamdeok, Woljeongri, Jungmun Saekdal)</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p>Signature summer events: Jeju Light Art Festa, Stepping Stone Music Festival, Jeju Food Festival</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p>Scenic hikes on Mount Hallasan, flower fields, and theme parks like Jeju Shinhwa World</p></li></ul><p> </p><p>Visa note: Vietnamese citizens can stay 30 days visa-free if flying directly to Jeju (via Jeju International Airport or port).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><img src=\"https://travelplusvn.com/public/uploads/images/POST/T07/where/05.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\"></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><h2>5. Travel to Europe â Golden Days of Summer</h2><p> </p><p>July is one of the most beautiful months to visit Europe, with sunny skies (15â30Â°C), long days, and countless outdoor events.</p><p> </p><p>Top highlights:</p><p> </p><ul><li><p>France: Lavender fields in Provence</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p>Greece: The iconic blue-and-white beauty of Santorini</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p>Italy: Romantic Tuscany with wine tasting and Renaissance art</p></li></ul><p> </p><ul><li><p>Austria, Denmark, Hungary: Lively street festivals, music, and culinary experiences</p></li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p><img src=\"https://travelplusvn.com/public/uploads/images/POST/T07/where/06.png\" loading=\"lazy\"></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Suggested itinerary: 10â14 days, visiting 3â4 countries.</p><p><br>Travel tip: Book entry tickets for top landmarks early (e.g., Vatican, Louvre, Colosseum), as summer crowds are huge.</p>','Where to Travel in July? Top Domestic & International Destinations for Summer','July is the perfect time for summer travel, relaxation, and creating unforgettable memories. It’s the peak of the holiday season for students in Vietnam, and many places around the world are enjoying their most beautiful time of the year.','2026-06-05 15:58:49','2026-06-05 15:58:49'),(27,14,'vi','DU LỊCH BỤI HAY DU LỊCH HƯỞNG THỤ – LỰA CHỌN PHONG CÁCH DU LỊCH PHÙ HỢP CHO BẠN','du-lich-bui-hay-du-lich-huong-thu-lua-chon-phong-cach-du-lich-phu-hop-cho-ban','Du lịch bụi mang đến trải nghiệm tự do, khám phá; du lịch hưởng thụ đem lại sự tiện nghi và thư giãn.','<h2><font color=\"#222222\" face=\"Roboto\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">TÃ¬m hiá»u sá»± khÃ¡c biá»t giá»¯a hai phong cÃ¡ch Äá» chá»n hÃ nh trÃ¬nh phÃ¹ há»£p cÃ¹ng Travel Plus.</span></font></h2><h2><br></h2><h2>Du lá»ch bá»¥i hay du lá»ch hÆ°á»ng thá»¥ â Hai trÆ°á»ng phÃ¡i Äá»i láº­p nhÆ°ng Äáº§y sá»©c hÃºt</h2><p> </p><p>Trong tháº¿ giá»